WEBVTT

00:00:00.750 --> 00:00:03.790
If you're depressed, you should go to a hospital. Why did you come to see me?

00:00:06.715 --> 00:00:10.301
Because you always make me smile, Jio.

00:00:12.137 --> 00:00:16.765
Wouldn't it be better to watch a comedy if you want to laugh? I'm not exactly a comedian.

00:00:16.766 --> 00:00:17.766
Sorry?

00:00:20.562 --> 00:00:21.562
Oh.

00:00:22.689 --> 00:00:26.276
I saw this on my way here and thought it was pretty, so I bought it for you, Jio.

00:00:29.279 --> 00:00:32.240
If you think it's pretty, you can just keep it.

00:00:32.942 --> 00:00:37.739
I don't really have much use for this, and I hate making trash.

00:00:42.250 --> 00:00:43.501
Jio.

00:00:44.002 --> 00:00:45.545
Are you...

00:00:46.171 --> 00:00:47.713
Angry?

00:00:47.714 --> 00:00:49.007
- What? - No.

00:00:49.549 --> 00:00:53.052
You seem a bit angry, unlike your usual self.

00:00:54.721 --> 00:00:58.265
I thought I was responding quite kindly today.

00:00:58.266 --> 00:01:01.060
Do I really have to hear that I look angry?

00:01:04.314 --> 00:01:07.442
I guess I came at a bad time today.

00:01:09.235 --> 00:01:11.196
I'll come back another time.

00:01:11.738 --> 00:01:13.281
You're just leaving?

00:01:17.076 --> 00:01:18.703
Jaeyoon...

00:01:21.498 --> 00:01:25.627
(Episode 4: Can't Hold Back Tonight)

00:01:31.508 --> 00:01:33.676
Jaeyoon hasn't called me at all.

00:01:33.968 --> 00:01:35.053
So?

00:01:36.137 --> 00:01:38.765
Boss, you've never been in a relationship, have you?

00:01:49.067 --> 00:01:51.027
You'd know if you'd kissed me.

00:01:52.153 --> 00:01:53.488
How was it?

00:01:55.615 --> 00:01:59.911
You can tell when you kiss someone whether it's their first kiss or not.

00:02:00.578 --> 00:02:03.205
It was your first kiss, wasn't it?

00:02:03.206 --> 00:02:04.541
No, it wasn't.

00:02:06.835 --> 00:02:08.378
It wasn't?

00:02:18.513 --> 00:02:19.556
Even now?

00:02:24.727 --> 00:02:26.062
Don't do this...

00:02:27.105 --> 00:02:28.398
Don't do what?

00:02:33.778 --> 00:02:35.405
I liked...

00:02:36.322 --> 00:02:37.365
Huh?

00:02:37.782 --> 00:02:40.535
I genuinely liked Jaeyoon.

00:02:53.715 --> 00:02:58.303
If the person I like doesn't like me back,

00:02:59.262 --> 00:03:01.014
It would be really sad.

00:03:02.223 --> 00:03:05.935
Then don't like him.

00:03:08.646 --> 00:03:09.647
What?

00:03:10.106 --> 00:03:14.652
If you don't like them in the first place, you won't get hurt.

00:03:15.069 --> 00:03:19.782
Stop wasting your time on such abstract emotions and focus on reality.

00:03:20.158 --> 00:03:21.993
And stop crying like an idiot.

00:03:23.036 --> 00:03:25.997
Boss, why can't you be honest with your feelings?

00:03:26.497 --> 00:03:30.877
What are you so afraid of that you build up such walls?

00:03:33.838 --> 00:03:35.965
Don't pretend to understand me.

00:03:51.064 --> 00:03:54.149
Well, I am affiliated with this place...

00:03:54.150 --> 00:03:58.112
Not exactly in an official capacity, but, uh...

00:03:59.197 --> 00:04:00.365
Yoon Jio!

00:04:00.740 --> 00:04:02.032
We have guests, guests!

00:04:02.033 --> 00:04:03.368
- We have guests. - So?

00:04:09.374 --> 00:04:10.500
Hey, hey!

00:04:12.502 --> 00:04:14.128
Why, you...

00:04:20.593 --> 00:04:23.054
Um, there are two of us. Do you happen to have a room?

00:04:24.555 --> 00:04:27.432
- Oh, Room 201 is empty. - Thank goodness.

00:04:27.433 --> 00:04:29.352
We'll take Room 201.

00:04:39.821 --> 00:04:42.698
Oh, President, why are you doing this yourself?

00:04:42.699 --> 00:04:48.037
Well, I am the boss, aren't I? I need to manage things around here.

00:04:48.663 --> 00:04:53.041
Why do you keep using formal language...? Ah, what's wrong with you lately?

00:04:53.042 --> 00:04:55.669
Ah, I'll do it, I'll do it, I'll do it.

00:04:55.670 --> 00:04:56.838
Ah,

00:04:57.171 --> 00:04:58.464
I'll do it.

00:04:59.173 --> 00:05:03.511
Step aside. I should do it. What do you mean, you'll do it?

00:05:06.681 --> 00:05:12.061
President, shall we start working? When should we list this property?

00:05:12.353 --> 00:05:15.063
Or should we call a contractor and remodel it first?

00:05:15.064 --> 00:05:19.694
No. Don't call anyone yet.

00:05:20.486 --> 00:05:22.612
I'm thinking of taking it slow.

00:05:22.613 --> 00:05:23.948
Ah...

00:05:24.532 --> 00:05:26.409
I can't believe you're delaying work.

00:05:27.577 --> 00:05:31.246
By any chance, is there something wrong with your...

00:05:31.247 --> 00:05:33.041
Call the contractor right now!

00:05:33.708 --> 00:05:37.377
List the property immediately! I gave you the order ages ago, why are you so slow?

00:05:37.378 --> 00:05:39.671
Hey, why do you keep bossing me around?

00:05:39.672 --> 00:05:43.301
I only listen to the President.

00:05:51.350 --> 00:05:53.935
Not now, later.

00:05:53.936 --> 00:05:55.020
Hey...

00:05:55.021 --> 00:05:56.606
Yes, President.

00:05:57.940 --> 00:05:59.358
You heard him, right?

00:06:05.865 --> 00:06:06.865
Huh.

00:06:08.785 --> 00:06:09.786
Yoon Jio.

00:06:10.495 --> 00:06:13.580
Why aren't you keeping your promise? Why aren't you playing my role properly?

00:06:13.581 --> 00:06:15.165
You're not doing my job properly either.

00:06:15.166 --> 00:06:16.959
You think I'm not doing your job?

00:06:17.543 --> 00:06:20.253
I just kindly welcomed the guests myself.

00:06:20.254 --> 00:06:21.255
What?

00:06:21.798 --> 00:06:23.298
We're fully booked.

00:06:23.299 --> 00:06:27.719
Check it properly. There was one empty room in the reservation system.

00:06:27.720 --> 00:06:28.720
Huh?

00:06:29.680 --> 00:06:31.057
That was...

00:06:37.188 --> 00:06:40.607
You should have asked me first. How could you give away your own room?

00:06:40.608 --> 00:06:42.652
You should have marked it beforehand!

00:06:43.027 --> 00:06:46.154
Why are you so terrible at everything you do?

00:06:46.155 --> 00:06:48.949
Hah, seriously... He's the one who messed up...

00:06:48.950 --> 00:06:51.035
What? 'He'?

00:06:52.286 --> 00:06:53.621
You sleep on the floor.

00:06:55.748 --> 00:06:58.668
What? How is that fair?

00:07:04.006 --> 00:07:07.260
Keep quiet. Stop tossing and turning.

00:07:17.061 --> 00:07:19.772
- What's that sound? - The wind.

00:07:20.481 --> 00:07:22.483
The wind is this loud?

00:07:22.984 --> 00:07:24.986
It's the ocean breeze.

00:07:28.447 --> 00:07:29.948
Are you scared?

00:07:29.949 --> 00:07:33.494
Why would I be scared? Don't be ridiculous...

00:07:44.297 --> 00:07:47.008
The ocean breeze sounds so loud

00:07:48.586 --> 00:07:51.672
Because the sea can't hold back what it wants to say.

00:07:52.513 --> 00:07:54.764
Everyone has nights like that.

00:07:54.765 --> 00:07:59.645
A night when you hold it all in alone, and you just can't hold it back anymore.

00:08:00.897 --> 00:08:04.817
A night when you want someone to listen to your story.

00:08:09.280 --> 00:08:12.450
Because the sea is so vast and deep,

00:08:13.534 --> 00:08:16.787
It holds many stories inside it.

00:08:18.664 --> 00:08:23.252
Badam Stay... Do you know what it means?

00:08:24.170 --> 00:08:25.421
What is it?

00:08:27.131 --> 00:08:30.550
It means a place to share a chat with the sea.

00:08:30.551 --> 00:08:36.140
Listening to the sea's stories, and telling stories I can't tell anyone else.

00:08:36.891 --> 00:08:41.520
How about it? The sound isn't so scary when you think about it like that, right?

00:08:45.566 --> 00:08:47.735
I was never scared in the first place.

00:09:02.083 --> 00:09:05.086
- Ugh... - Just come up and sleep on the bed.

00:09:07.088 --> 00:09:08.464
Really?

00:09:16.764 --> 00:09:18.266
Ah...

00:09:28.943 --> 00:09:32.363
Why did our souls switch?

00:09:32.989 --> 00:09:35.116
How should I know?

00:09:35.783 --> 00:09:38.119
Shouldn't there be a reason?

00:09:40.371 --> 00:09:45.501
It's like a car accident. Accidents don't have reasons.

00:09:51.465 --> 00:09:54.719
Let's try living as each other.

00:09:58.055 --> 00:10:02.435
Boss, you live as Yoon Jio, and I'll live as Cha Dokyung.

00:10:03.144 --> 00:10:05.437
If we live each other's lives,

00:10:05.438 --> 00:10:09.483
Wouldn't we get a hint on how to return to normal?

00:10:31.255 --> 00:10:37.762
"Check In to You"

